race.comment: Tough. KISS MY ROCK (4) is third-up and ready to fire back in grade. He's raced well in town over this trip and will likely take a sit today. Gets the nod in a competitive race. CHOSEN VENTURE (8) brings a decent number from his nose defeat at Swan Hill this grade/trip. He is still shy of his best and is on a quick back-up. A player. JOTOPELI (6) led and missed a nose this trip at Hamilton and then dropped back to a sprint and delivered his Maiden at this circuit. He will race forward and can make the finish in this line-up. LITTLEBITCHEEKY (2) may need it longer now, but he resumed in good order in SA in a 66 and has more up her sleeve. The claim helps with some of the weight hike, and she's capable of using the inside barrier. BALLON D'OR (1) has a low gate and handy 3kg claim and may benefit from the step-up to the mile. She raced as the favourite at Kyneton last time when beaten by less than 2L.
